# Portfolio HTML and component patterns

## BEM and styles

Use BEM-style class names; all component classes are defined in `styles.css`. Do not invent new class names for existing patterns.

## Canonical sources

- **Full page example:** `disney-case-study.html` — long-form case study structure: hero + My Role block, Jump To nav, flat case-block sections (no cards), outcome metrics, blockquote, and footer with Say hello + nav. Use as reference for new case studies.
- **Pattern library:** `patterns.html` — documents all patterns. “Case study sections” documents hero + My Role, Jump To nav, case-block, outcome metrics, case-quote, and numbered list. Source snippets live in `components/`.
- **Component snippets:** `components/` — `case-hero.html`, `case-hero-with-role.html`, `case-study-shell.html`, `header.html`, `header-case.html`, `footer.html`, `footer-case.html`. Use or adapt when adding content.
- **Style guide:** `style-guide.html` — typography, colors, and UI specs.

## When adding or editing pages

Prefer copying or composing from the component files and `disney-case-study.html` so markup and class names match. Only add new classes when introducing a genuinely new pattern, and keep BEM naming.
